                    <p>EXCLAMATIO expressing surprise or amazement.</p>
                    <p> 歎稱法，贊稱法 Emphatic reference to something with an attendant expression of the
                        speaker's amazement at it, and the expected astonishment of the audience. </p>
                    <p>Easy to confuse with EXCLAMATIO which focusses on plain exclamatory
                        expression of the speaker's emotion</p>
                    <p>Late Greek: thaumasmos.</p>
